  "prompt": "Who are some famous INFJs?",
  "response": "INFJ (Introverted, Intuitive, Feeling, Judging) is one of the 16 personality types identified by the Myers-Briggs Type Indicator (MBTI). INFJs are often described as insightful, creative, and idealistic. Here are some famous individuals who are often cited as likely INFJs:\n\n1. **Martin Luther King Jr.** - Civil rights leader and advocate for nonviolent resistance.\n2. **Nelson Mandela** - Anti-apartheid revolutionary and former President of South Africa.\n3. **Mother Teresa** - Catholic nun and missionary known for her charitable work.\n4. **Carl Jung** - Swiss psychiatrist and psychoanalyst who founded analytical psychology.\n5. **Fyodor Dostoevsky** - Renowned Russian novelist and philosopher.\n6. **Nicole Kidman** - Academy Award-winning actress.\n7. **Kristen Stewart** - Actress best known for her role in the \"Twilight\" series.\n8. **Daniel Day-Lewis** - Acclaimed actor known for his intense method acting.\n9. **Cate Blanchett** - Award-winning actress with a diverse range of roles.\n10. **Tori Amos** - Singer-songwriter and pianist known for her emotional and introspective music.\n11. **Mary Wollstonecraft** - Philosopher and early advocate for women's rights.\n12. **Lionel Messi** - World-renowned soccer player, often considered one of the greatest of all time.\n13. **Eleanor Roosevelt** - Former First Lady of the United States and human rights advocate.\n14. **Mahatma Gandhi** - Leader of the Indian independence movement and proponent of nonviolent resistance.\n15. **Emily Bront\u00eb** - Author of the classic novel \"Wuthering Heights.\"\n\nIt's important to note that these assessments are based on public personas and interpretations, and precise personality typing can be subjective.",
